389
00:34:17,894 --> 00:34:23,956
Motions, orders, and resolutions 26061 offered by President Behrs, annual budget process for fiscal 27.

390
00:34:24,716 --> 00:34:28,317
We just discussed this at 6 p.m., but we have our annual budget for fiscal 27.

391
00:34:28,357 --> 00:34:31,838
This is for the city's general fund and the water sewer enterprise fund.

392
00:34:32,819 --> 00:34:41,222
Be it resolved by the city council that based on the budget ordinance and discussions with the administration, the city council and city administration will follow the following budget schedule for the fiscal 27 city budget.

393
00:34:42,662 --> 00:34:47,484
By March 11th, City Councilors submit individual budget recommendations for consideration in Committee of the Whole.

394
00:34:48,524 --> 00:34:53,786
Just tonight, Tuesday, March 24th at 6 p.m., we had a Committee of the Whole meeting to discuss our budget recommendations.

395
00:34:54,546 --> 00:34:58,327
Right now is our City Council regular meeting to submit collective budget recommendation.

396
00:34:58,968 --> 00:35:06,150
On April 8th at 6 p.m., we'll have a joint meeting of the City Council and School Committee to receive a financial update and discuss the fiscal 27 budget process.

397
00:35:07,022 --> 00:35:17,435
From April 15th to May 15th, the City Council will hold its preliminary budget meetings with department heads, and by Friday, May 31st, the Mayor will submit the comprehensive budget proposal to the City Council.

398
00:35:18,505 --> 00:35:32,958
Be it further resolved that a draft schedule of preliminary budget meetings and committee of the whole is as follows, Wednesday, April 15th, Tuesday, April 21st, Tuesday, April 28th, Wednesday, April 29th, Tuesday, May 5th, Wednesday, May 6th, Tuesday, May 12th, and Wednesday, May 13th.

399
00:35:33,058 --> 00:35:35,380
Those are all at 6 p.m.

400
00:35:35,861 --> 00:35:41,005
We may not use all of them, but they are available to us.

401
00:35:44,839 --> 00:35:47,061
That is the motion and schedule.

402
00:35:47,181 --> 00:35:47,701
At 6 p.m.

403
00:35:47,742 --> 00:35:56,489
we talked about our budget recommendations, and I think really at this point the path forward is, you know, I went through our compiled collective recommendation.

404
00:35:56,529 --> 00:36:04,055
It seems like much of what we included last time still has not happened, so we want to keep recommending that the city do those things.

405
00:36:06,467 --> 00:36:09,790
I'll just quickly go over those for folks who weren't able to be in our last meeting.

406
00:36:10,471 --> 00:36:16,977
The first recommendation is that we maintain full level service funding for our public schools and city departments.

407
00:36:17,798 --> 00:36:21,001
So that means that we do not have service cuts at our schools or our city.

408
00:36:21,902 --> 00:36:27,564
And then the second one is to fund our assessing department to implement the residential exemption.

409
00:36:28,064 --> 00:36:45,111
And also I'm going to incorporate a bit of Councilor Scarpelli's recommendation around making sure that we can support our seniors, veterans, people with disabilities, folks who may need assistance in accessing exemptions and other assistance from our assessing department.

410
00:36:46,376 --> 00:36:54,783
Third item is increasing funding for our DPW and facilities for improved street repair and safety, tree planting, and capital improvements.

411
00:36:55,503 --> 00:37:14,137
That includes a number of items including funding street repair and safety improvements, additional traffic engineers and transportation planning, more re-striping, patching of potholes, fixing sidewalks, installing and maintaining road safety markings, and bike-related equipment.

412
00:37:14,918 --> 00:37:25,921
Funding our urban tree management plan, enabling volunteers to finally get our volunteer tree planting program off the ground so that we can start putting more trees up in our neighborhoods.

413
00:37:26,921 --> 00:37:38,644
And funding to improve snow removal, including priority sidewalks and bus stops moving forward to understand how we can implement a priority sidewalk clearing program.

414
00:37:41,344 --> 00:37:43,445
Funding our citywide inclusion specialist.

415
00:37:44,708 --> 00:37:47,294
funding the fire department dive team training and equipment.

416
00:37:47,979 --> 00:37:50,981
And then there were four new items to be included.

417
00:37:52,022 --> 00:38:10,274
One was addressing the increase in part-time librarian pay and supporting our library staff, additional funding for arts and culture organizations, and making sure that our Medford Family Network, which is facing a serious funding gap, moves forward with the funding that it needs to continue its amazing work.

418
00:38:10,854 --> 00:38:14,477
And then finally, funding our city messenger and council assistant.

419
00:38:15,137 --> 00:38:22,642
So that's the general outline I have I don't have the final document obviously because we just talked about it you know around 615.

420
00:38:24,884 --> 00:38:30,548
But I'm interested in hearing from counselors what they would prefer in terms of a process going forward.

421
00:38:31,469 --> 00:38:31,749
I could.

422
00:38:32,587 --> 00:38:37,749
take that outline, write it up and have the clerk submit that to the mayor and also share that with members of the council.

423
00:38:38,329 --> 00:38:48,633
I could also draft that and have the clerk distribute it for comments by members of the council before we submit it, or I could write a draft and we could discuss that at an upcoming meeting.

424
00:38:48,813 --> 00:38:52,754
So whichever of those three options folks would prefer, I'm happy to do.

425
00:38:53,134 --> 00:38:53,854
Councilor Scarpelli.

426
00:38:54,595 --> 00:39:01,497
Council President, I think that you've done your due diligence having these pre-budget meetings, having the council,

427
00:39:03,308 --> 00:39:04,949
share what our wishes are.

428
00:39:05,329 --> 00:39:06,609
I think we discussed that.

429
00:39:07,090 --> 00:39:14,352
I think that the sooner that it's in the administration's hands, the sooner we get some answers so we can move this budget process forward.

430
00:39:14,372 --> 00:39:18,853
So I would go with your first option.

431
00:39:19,433 --> 00:39:28,116
If my colleagues would support that, that's what I would move forward with that assessment, Mr. President.

432
00:39:29,281 --> 00:39:29,461
Great.

433
00:39:29,761 --> 00:39:31,002
Thank you, Councilor Scarpelli.

434
00:39:31,362 --> 00:39:35,064
