Thank you, Mr. President.

653
00:55:18,607 --> 00:55:23,892
Just for a quick synopsis, I know people have been reaching out saying, George, why do we, why does the council do this?

654
00:55:23,952 --> 00:55:33,479
And I think that it started back in, perhaps you remember, during the pandemic, we had to protect our brick and mortar businesses and

655
00:55:34,640 --> 00:55:45,622
from outside vendors to come in from outside the city without putting in the proper paperwork and due diligence and commitment to the community.

656
00:55:46,241 --> 00:55:49,682
So we really use that to protect our brick and mortar businesses.

657
00:55:49,742 --> 00:55:56,545
And this is the process that we look at and that we've been working with, and I think it's been working fine.

658
00:55:57,185 --> 00:55:58,025
We did have a question.

659
00:55:58,065 --> 00:56:03,187
The reason why it was brought up, because the petition looked like it was from April to August.

660
00:56:03,227 --> 00:56:09,930
So it looked like it was, but it's just a breakdown is for the Boston Glory games, I believe.

661
00:56:10,010 --> 00:56:14,632
So I believe it's Sundays or Saturdays throughout,

662
00:56:16,570 --> 00:56:19,492
uh, April through, um, through August.

663
00:56:19,612 --> 00:56:21,793
So, um, I see everything in order.

664
00:56:21,853 --> 00:56:23,294
All the paperwork is in order.

665
00:56:23,734 --> 00:56:25,735
I would move approval, Mr President.

666
00:56:25,855 --> 00:56:36,461
It's common practice now, and it provides a great experience for all of our residents that have the opportunity to go watch Glory game over at Hormel.

667
00:56:36,641 --> 00:56:38,682
So I move approval.

668
00:56:39,570 --> 00:56:40,531
Thank you, Councillor Scarpelli.

669
00:56:40,551 --> 00:56:42,812
And it looks like we have Luke from the Boston Glory here.

670
00:56:42,872 --> 00:56:51,016
Luke, I don't know if you want to say anything about your season and how many games, how many weekends you'll be here and what, you know, what Charlie Dogs is.

671
00:56:51,056 --> 00:56:54,198
But if you'd like to speak to that, you're more than welcome to.

672
00:56:55,459 --> 00:56:56,580
And I can ask you to unmute.

673
00:57:01,022 --> 00:57:02,063
Yeah, thanks.

674
00:57:02,183 --> 00:57:06,125
So yeah, we'll have six to seven games depending on the playoffs at Hormel this year.

675
00:57:06,793 --> 00:57:09,954
First one is April 25th, I believe.

676
00:57:11,054 --> 00:57:16,395
Last possible one is the first weekend of August, but it might end up being end of July based on the playoffs.

677
00:57:17,335 --> 00:57:22,056
And yeah, Trolley Dogs is the vendor that comes and serves food to all our fans.

678
00:57:22,836 --> 00:57:23,856
It's a great time.

679
00:57:23,896 --> 00:57:24,896
I highly suggest y'all come.

680
00:57:26,616 --> 00:57:26,936
Awesome.

681
00:57:27,516 --> 00:57:29,117
Well, thank you, Luke.

682
00:57:29,397 --> 00:57:32,117
On the motion of Councilor Scarpelli to approve, seconded by?

683
00:57:33,377 --> 00:57:34,438
Seconded by Councilor Callahan.

684
00:57:34,518 --> 00:57:35,338
